{"lemma":"رَيّانِ","slug":"رَيّانِ","root":"ر.#.#","root_slug":"ر-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17177","n17198"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%91%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"plump, fleshy"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"well-irrigated, well-watered"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Bāb al-Rayyān (one of the gates of Jannat (paradise), for those who fasted)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Rayyan or Ryan"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From رَيّ (rayy, “watering”) + ـَان (-ān)."},"ipa":["/raj.jaːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17177","headword_ar":"رَيَّانُ","root":"rwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoyaAnu","text_ar":"رَوْيَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] an epithet from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawiYa","text_ar":"رَوِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, M, Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Satisfied with drinking"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of water and of milk &c.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having drunk"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thereof]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enough to quench,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfy, his thirst; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaTo$aAnu","text_ar":"عَطْشَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh: *) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray~aA","text_ar":"رَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the word is an epithet; for it is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"only in a subst., of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolaY","text_ar":"فَعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the final radical, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqowaY","text_ar":"تَقْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so that if it were a subst., it would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raw~aY","text_ar":"رَوَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoyaA","text_ar":"رَوْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) as to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray~aA","text_ar":"رَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is thought to be used as the proper name of a woman, it is, thus used, an epithet, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaArivu","text_ar":"الحَارِثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEab~aAsu","text_ar":"العَبَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though without the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, * M:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwaA='N","text_ar":"روَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) with kesr and medd., (S,) in measure like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbN","text_ar":"كِتَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) masc. and fem. (Mgh, Msb.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN riwaA='N mina AlmaA='i","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ رِوَا=ءٌ مِنَ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, satisfied with drinking of water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabotN ray~aAnu","text_ar":"نَبْتٌ رَيَّانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarN riwaA='N","text_ar":"شَجَرٌ رِوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees, having plentiful irrigation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flourishing and fresh, luxuriant, juicy, succulent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sappy, by reason of plentiful irrigation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see the verb]. (M.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray~aAnu","text_ar":"رَيَّانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Full of fat and flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JM.) And you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajohN ray~aAnu","text_ar":"وَجْهٌ رَيَّانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plump face"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; an expression of dispraise [app. when relating to a man, but not otherwise; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray~aAnu","text_ar":"رَيَّانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray~aA","text_ar":"رَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a youth, or to a woman, or a limb of a woman, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plump and juicy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used by way of praise]: opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajohN ZamoA=nu","text_ar":"وَجْهٌ ظَمْا=نُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZmA^","text_ar":"ظما"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN ray~aA Almuxaloxali","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ رَيَّا المُخَلْخَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman full,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plump, in the place of the anklet"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (JM.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN ray~aAnu AlZ~ahori","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ رَيَّانُ الظَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse fat in the portion of flesh and sinew next the back-bone on each side."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Mgh","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n17198","headword_ar":"رَيَّانُ","root":"rY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwY","text_ar":"روى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}